         <head>To <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2045.xml"/>Richard Tompson</persName></head>
         <opener><placeName>London</placeName><lb/><date when="1759-08-22">August 22, 1759</date><lb/><lb/>
            <salute/>
         </opener>
         <p>I am afraid you would hardly save yourself harmless, by the publication of those
               letters.<note place="foot" n="1"><persName><ref target="/persons/pers2045.xml"
                  />Tompson</persName> included this letter in the preface to his publication of the
               interchange of letters between him and <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"
                  />JW</persName> in <date from="1755" to="1756">1755â€“56</date>.</note> However, if
            you are inclined to run the hazard, I do not object. Only it would be needful to
            advertise the readers, that what I wrote was in haste, just as I could snatch a little
            time now and then, to answer the private letter of a private friend, without any thought
            of its going any farther.</p>
         <closer>I am,<lb/>
            <signed>Your affectionate brother,<lb/><persName>J. Wesley</persName></signed></closer>
      </body>
